The Ukrainians targeted the courthouse in Lysychansk with a HIMARS artillery attack, where the 6th regiment from Russia's second army corps had set up their headquarters. The strike is reported to have killed at least 50 officers and soldiers. Anton Gerashchenko, an advisor to the Ukrainian Interior Ministry, tweeted: "Ukrainian Army made a high-precision hit with HIMARS on a court building in occupied Lysychansk where about 50 high-profile Russian military were at that moment. This was confirmed by intelligence and head of Luhansk Military Administration." FOLLOW UPDATES BELOW